\newlabel{fig:ageint-scholarship-triangulation-map}{{17}{142}{The scholarship triangulation map shows how generated AGEINT sections move from citation presence through source-family classification, thin-support gates, single-family review warnings, and current artifact-evidence reports. Its reader value is to make scholarship triangulation map fields, row and column obligations, source records, reviewer decisions, and closure evidence visible at a glance, with the curriculum orientation as the source section and defensive review as the boundary}{figure.caption.19}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {18}{\ignorespaces The Synthetic Tradecraft System Atlas replaces the former graphical abstract with a governed-system view of AGEINT. It shows the source spine as the evidence floor; intelligence disciplines as collection and context lanes; Synthetic Analytic Tradecraft as the central claim-making contract; bounded agentic assistance as a limited support layer; and verification, safety, and human-review gates as the outer assurance ring. The figure is a curriculum architecture map, not a claim that AGEINT has measured field capability or learning outcomes.}}{143}{figure.caption.20}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-graphical-abstract}{{18}{143}{The Synthetic Tradecraft System Atlas replaces the former graphical abstract with a governed-system view of AGEINT. It shows the source spine as the evidence floor; intelligence disciplines as collection and context lanes; Synthetic Analytic Tradecraft as the central claim-making contract; bounded agentic assistance as a limited support layer; and verification, safety, and human-review gates as the outer assurance ring. The figure is a curriculum architecture map, not a claim that AGEINT has measured field capability or learning outcomes}{figure.caption.20}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {19}{\ignorespaces The method-contract figure makes AGEINT's Synthetic Analytic Tradecraft claim falsifiable. It links source-family triangulation, synthetic fixtures, analytic field separation, negative-control testing, reviewer challenge, and artifact-evidence reports so early manuscript claims remain method commitments rather than prestige language. Its reader value is to make synthetic tradecraft method contract labels, source records, review gates, refresh cues, and reader-use boundaries visible at a glance, with the curriculum orientation as the source section and defensive review as the boundary.}}{144}{figure.caption.21}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-synthetic-tradecraft-method-contract}{{19}{144}{The method-contract figure makes AGEINT's Synthetic Analytic Tradecraft claim falsifiable. It links source-family triangulation, synthetic fixtures, analytic field separation, negative-control testing, reviewer challenge, and artifact-evidence reports so early manuscript claims remain method commitments rather than prestige language. Its reader value is to make synthetic tradecraft method contract labels, source records, review gates, refresh cues, and reader-use boundaries visible at a glance, with the curriculum orientation as the source section and defensive review as the boundary}{figure.caption.21}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {20}{\ignorespaces The analysis-validation matrix makes the manuscript's scholarship and assurance claims reviewable by class. It separates design guidance, empirical or evaluation claims, governance claims, figure/readability claims, rendered-artifact readiness claims, and reviewer disposition claims so each one has a required evidence packet, validation question, failure condition, and remediation path.}}{145}{figure.caption.22}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-analysis-validation-matrix}{{20}{145}{The analysis-validation matrix makes the manuscript's scholarship and assurance claims reviewable by class. It separates design guidance, empirical or evaluation claims, governance claims, figure/readability claims, rendered-artifact readiness claims, and reviewer disposition claims so each one has a required evidence packet, validation question, failure condition, and remediation path}{figure.caption.22}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {21}{\ignorespaces The analysis-validation family-coverage figure closes the gap between method prose and generated manuscript structure. It maps each claim-bearing manuscript family to a canonical analysis-validation lane, the evidence signal that should be present, and the failure signal that should block local readiness if a family becomes claim-bearing without a review class.}}{146}{figure.caption.23}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-analysis-validation-family-coverage}{{21}{146}{The analysis-validation family-coverage figure closes the gap between method prose and generated manuscript structure. It maps each claim-bearing manuscript family to a canonical analysis-validation lane, the evidence signal that should be present, and the failure signal that should block local readiness if a family becomes claim-bearing without a review class}{figure.caption.23}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {22}{\ignorespaces The source metadata integrity figure makes the anchor-lane hardening contract visible to reviewers. It separates curated intelligence anchors, source-quality support anchors, explicit lane and tier fields, refresh cadence evidence, denominator context, reviewer action, and the artifact-evidence manifest failure path so source rows cannot silently fall back to broad domain or source-type semantics while the rendered PDF still appears locally ready. Read it as local metadata telemetry, not a quality score for the cited sources.}}{147}{figure.caption.24}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-source-metadata-integrity}{{22}{147}{The source metadata integrity figure makes the anchor-lane hardening contract visible to reviewers. It separates curated intelligence anchors, source-quality support anchors, explicit lane and tier fields, refresh cadence evidence, denominator context, reviewer action, and the artifact-evidence manifest failure path so source rows cannot silently fall back to broad domain or source-type semantics while the rendered PDF still appears locally ready. Read it as local metadata telemetry, not a quality score for the cited sources}{figure.caption.24}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {23}{\ignorespaces The claim-calibration verifier figure makes the final RedTeam/Science hardening layer visible: high-risk manuscript claims are separated into empirical, governance, visualization, artifact-readiness, safety, and formalism lanes; each lane must show direct support or explicit boundary language; weak source-guide context cannot carry measured-performance or statistical claims alone; and figure metadata must state semantic role, evidence role, quantitative status, denominator, counting rule, reviewer action, and interpretation limit before the artifact-evidence manifest can pass. Compare the local manuscript, registry, source-support, and report surfaces as reviewer inputs; do not read the visual as a score, benchmark, or empirical performance claim.}}{148}{figure.caption.25}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-claim-calibration-and-visual-semantics}{{23}{148}{The claim-calibration verifier figure makes the final RedTeam/Science hardening layer visible: high-risk manuscript claims are separated into empirical, governance, visualization, artifact-readiness, safety, and formalism lanes; each lane must show direct support or explicit boundary language; weak source-guide context cannot carry measured-performance or statistical claims alone; and figure metadata must state semantic role, evidence role, quantitative status, denominator, counting rule, reviewer action, and interpretation limit before the artifact-evidence manifest can pass. Compare the local manuscript, registry, source-support, and report surfaces as reviewer inputs; do not read the visual as a score, benchmark, or empirical performance claim}{figure.caption.25}{}}
