\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {47}{\ignorespaces The OSINT sequence separates public-source discovery from claim reuse: each handoff records provenance, legality, minimization, corroboration, caveats, and reviewer disposition before a bounded judgment can be logged. In the open source intelligence osint / osint foundations section, it lets readers compare requirement owner, discovery analyst, provenance reviewer, legal and minimization gate, corroboration reviewer, final reviewer, logged bounded judgment, stop-and-retire path for unverifiable or out-of-bounds evidence so the visual functions as a traceable course aid rather than an unscoped assertion.}}{312}{figure.caption.49}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:osint-collection-to-verification-pipeline}{{47}{312}{The OSINT sequence separates public-source discovery from claim reuse: each handoff records provenance, legality, minimization, corroboration, caveats, and reviewer disposition before a bounded judgment can be logged. In the open source intelligence osint / osint foundations section, it lets readers compare requirement owner, discovery analyst, provenance reviewer, legal and minimization gate, corroboration reviewer, final reviewer, logged bounded judgment, stop-and-retire path for unverifiable or out-of-bounds evidence so the visual functions as a traceable course aid rather than an unscoped assertion}{figure.caption.49}{}}
