\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {89}{\ignorespaces This diagram shows how each AGEINT design pattern is converted into a documented, auditable governance artifact rather than an operational deployment. In the ageint agentic intelligence / ageint design patterns and archetypes section, it lets readers compare A top-to-bottom transform. A raw design motif enters a governance intake. It splits into four parallel artifacts: a safe registry entry, a provenance, evidence record, and an interface contract so the visual functions as a traceable course aid rather than an unscoped assertion.}}{731}{figure.caption.91}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:design-motif-to-safe-registry-transform}{{89}{731}{This diagram shows how each AGEINT design pattern is converted into a documented, auditable governance artifact rather than an operational deployment. In the ageint agentic intelligence / ageint design patterns and archetypes section, it lets readers compare A top-to-bottom transform. A raw design motif enters a governance intake. It splits into four parallel artifacts: a safe registry entry, a provenance, evidence record, and an interface contract so the visual functions as a traceable course aid rather than an unscoped assertion}{figure.caption.91}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {90}{\ignorespaces The pattern taxonomy groups AGEINT design patterns by safe curriculum role. The captioned view belongs to the ageint agentic intelligence / ageint design patterns and archetypes section and should be read as a map of pattern taxonomy categories, denominators, evidence lanes, limitations, and reviewer-use cautions, not as a capability score or live-task instruction.}}{732}{figure.caption.92}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-pattern-taxonomy}{{90}{732}{The pattern taxonomy groups AGEINT design patterns by safe curriculum role. The captioned view belongs to the ageint agentic intelligence / ageint design patterns and archetypes section and should be read as a map of pattern taxonomy categories, denominators, evidence lanes, limitations, and reviewer-use cautions, not as a capability score or live-task instruction}{figure.caption.92}{}}
