\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {120}{\ignorespaces This diagram walks through the structured analytic sequence that scores evidence against rival hypotheses to find the one with the least disconfirming evidence, under formal tradecraft standards. It is anchored to the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section; use it to inspect A workflow. Frame the analytic question feeds enumeration of a full set of competing hypotheses, in parallel, collection of evidence, and assumptions. Both feed a hypothesis-by-evidence . Each cell is rated for consistency or inconsistency. Diagnostic evidence is identified. The least-disconfirmed hypothesis is selected. A sensitivity check tests reliance on key items: if findings are not robust while preserving the distinction between curriculum structure, evidence boundary, and accountable practice.}}{979}{figure.caption.122}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:competing-hypotheses-analysis-workflow}{{120}{979}{This diagram walks through the structured analytic sequence that scores evidence against rival hypotheses to find the one with the least disconfirming evidence, under formal tradecraft standards. It is anchored to the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section; use it to inspect A workflow. Frame the analytic question feeds enumeration of a full set of competing hypotheses, in parallel, collection of evidence, and assumptions. Both feed a hypothesis-by-evidence . Each cell is rated for consistency or inconsistency. Diagnostic evidence is identified. The least-disconfirmed hypothesis is selected. A sensitivity check tests reliance on key items: if findings are not robust while preserving the distinction between curriculum structure, evidence boundary, and accountable practice}{figure.caption.122}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {121}{\ignorespaces Source-backed conceptual schematic comparing the source classes behind analytic-tradecraft claims: professional standards, official reform and postmortems, SAT catalogues, empirical SAT studies, forecasting calibration, and AI reasoning-support programs. The denominator is AGEINT's curated analytic-tradecraft anchor set, and the figure fails closed when doctrine, adoption, or postmortem pressure becomes an empirical accuracy score or universal debiasing overclaim.}}{980}{figure.caption.123}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-analytic-tradecraft-evidence-ladder}{{121}{980}{Source-backed conceptual schematic comparing the source classes behind analytic-tradecraft claims: professional standards, official reform and postmortems, SAT catalogues, empirical SAT studies, forecasting calibration, and AI reasoning-support programs. The denominator is AGEINT's curated analytic-tradecraft anchor set, and the figure fails closed when doctrine, adoption, or postmortem pressure becomes an empirical accuracy score or universal debiasing overclaim}{figure.caption.123}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {122}{\ignorespaces Source-backed conceptual schematic comparing SAT purpose, doctrine, classroom artifacts, adoption studies, technique-specific experiments, ACH critiques, and decision-science complements. The local artifact set is the chapter 41 SAT lesson and its curated anchors; the figure fails closed on overclaim language that treats SATs as a proven universal bias remedy, an empirical score, or a replacement for analyst accountability.}}{981}{figure.caption.124}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-sat-evidence-boundary}{{122}{981}{Source-backed conceptual schematic comparing SAT purpose, doctrine, classroom artifacts, adoption studies, technique-specific experiments, ACH critiques, and decision-science complements. The local artifact set is the chapter 41 SAT lesson and its curated anchors; the figure fails closed on overclaim language that treats SATs as a proven universal bias remedy, an empirical score, or a replacement for analyst accountability}{figure.caption.124}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {123}{\ignorespaces Source-backed conceptual schematic decomposing analytic tradecraft claims while separating observation, inference, assumption, likelihood, confidence, dissent, and decision-boundary fields before any manuscript claim is treated as reviewable. Its reader value is to make Observation what the source says, Evidence quality access, reliability, gap, Inference what analyst adds, and Assumption register what must be true visible at a glance, with the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section as the source section and defensive review as the boundary.}}{982}{figure.caption.125}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-first-principles-tradecraft-decomposition}{{123}{982}{Source-backed conceptual schematic decomposing analytic tradecraft claims while separating observation, inference, assumption, likelihood, confidence, dissent, and decision-boundary fields before any manuscript claim is treated as reviewable. Its reader value is to make Observation what the source says, Evidence quality access, reliability, gap, Inference what analyst adds, and Assumption register what must be true visible at a glance, with the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section as the source section and defensive review as the boundary}{figure.caption.125}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {124}{\ignorespaces Source-backed evidence-derived chart from local research-anchor metadata showing official, standards, statutory, postmortem, scholarly evaluation, and forecasting evidence lanes for analytic-tradecraft claims. The captioned view belongs to the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section and should be read as a map of analytic source quality boundary categories, denominators, evidence lanes, limitations, and reviewer-use cautions, not as a capability score or live-task instruction.}}{983}{figure.caption.126}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ageint-analytic-source-quality-boundary}{{124}{983}{Source-backed evidence-derived chart from local research-anchor metadata showing official, standards, statutory, postmortem, scholarly evaluation, and forecasting evidence lanes for analytic-tradecraft claims. The captioned view belongs to the epistemic rigor and analytic tradecraft / structured analytic techniques sats section and should be read as a map of analytic source quality boundary categories, denominators, evidence lanes, limitations, and reviewer-use cautions, not as a capability score or live-task instruction}{figure.caption.126}{}}
